    182          /***************************************************************************//**
    183           *   When EM4 pin retention is set to power_manager_pin_retention_latch,
    184           *   then pins are retained through EM4 entry and wakeup. The pin state is
    185           *   released by calling this function. The feature allows peripherals or
    186           *   GPIO to be re-initialized after EM4 exit (reset), and when
    187           *   initialization is done, this function can release pins and return
    188           *   control to the peripherals or GPIO.
    189           ******************************************************************************/

   \                                 In section .text, align 2, keep-with-next
